stylometry: When placing an order, you need to take the size, type, storage costs, etc. into consideration.  Again, you want to order enough that you can run efficiently, but not too much that the costs incurred are too high.  If the goods are perishable, they only have a certain shelf life, and you can not keep them stored for an extended period of time.  Another larde consideration is whether a product is seasonal.  If in season the product is much more expensive, then a company would try to order around the season to avoid extra costs.  If it is only available in that season, then they need to make sure that they order enough to fill their present and future needs.
